{{nihongo|'''Kurozuka Kofun'''|黒塚古墳|}} is a [[Kofun period]] [[:en:Zenpokoenfun|keyhole-shaped Kofun]], located in the Yanagimoto-cho neighborhood of the city of [[:en:Tenri, Nara|Tenri, Nara]] in the [[:en:Kansai region|Kansai region]] of [[:en:Japan|Japan]]. The tumulus was designated a [[Monuments of Japan|National Historic Site of Japan]] in 2001.<ref name="Bunka1">{{cite web |url=https://bunka.nii.ac.jp/heritages/detail/192522|title=黒塚古墳|language=ja |publisher=Agency for Cultural Affairs |accessdate=August 20, 2024}}</ref> It is noted for the 33 triangular-rimmed [[:en:Bronze mirror|Bronze mirror]]s with divine beasts that were excavated in almost the same arrangement as when they were originally buried.
==Overview== The Kurozuka Kofun is a {{nihongo|''zenpō-kōen-fun''|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|2=ja|3=前方後円墳|4=ko|5=전방후원분|6=zh|7=前方後圓墳|lt=Zenpokoenfun|comement=second one attempting to fix this error|lt=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|comment=doing this because I need to differentiate it in piped links too with my new interwiki tool as not the ambiguous phrase keyhole shaped kofun|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=[[Zenpokoenfun]]|2=前方後円墳|3=|4=}}, which is shaped like a keyhole, having one square end and one circular end, when viewed from above. It belongs to the Yanagimoto Kofun Group in the southeastern part of the Nara Basin, and is orientated to the west. The tumulus has a total length of about 130 meters. The posterior circular mound has a diameter about 72 meters and height of about dd meters and is constructed in three tiers. The anterior rectangular portion has a length of about 48 meters, height of 6 meters and is constructed in two tiers. A slight arc-shaped bulge can be seen in the front of the front circular mound, indicating that it is shaped like a drumstick. These are characteristics of early Kofun period. The tumulus has a moat. No traces of ''[[fukiishi]]'' or ''[[:en:Haniwa|Haniwa]]'' have been found.<ref name="Shiseki">{{cite book |last1=Isomura |first1=Yukio |last2=Sakai |first2=Hideya |title=(国指定史跡事典) National Historic Site Encyclopedia |date=2012 |publisher=学生社 |isbn=978-43dd750403}}{{in lang|ja}}</ref>
